# fixed mindset - if it doesn't work this way it won't work, you either know how to do something or don't
# growth mindset - learn from things that don't work. "I struggled with something and learned about it, so which my brain learning"
# "I liked that you struggled with the problem" isn't a bad thing, it's positive as it's showing you're TRYING to push through
#  it and make progress


brain working:
# focused - when you're actually paying attention to what you're doing and internalising it
# diffused - more subconscious, but you'll chew through things you did when focused without thinking
# about it too much and this sometimes can lead to solutions (shower thoughts...)


WHY ISN'T IT WORKING?
# Google, because someone probably had the same problem, asked about it and got a solutions
# Take a break and come back to it - revisit it when your brain has had chance to chill
# Ask for help! Show your working.


No deadlines:
# Not a structured class
# Adds additional stress for no reason
# Can be fun to set a self imposed goal, but there is plenty of time 



