# XY Problem - asking for X, thinking you need to do Y, implementing Y and then it not actually being relevant or useful for X at all

# 5 Things To Ask:
	# Provide a link to your project or lesson
	# Provide existing code (see above)
	# Explain the problem and what steps are needed to reproduce it
	# Describe what you're expecting to happen and why you're expecting this to happen from what you've coded
	# Summarize what's already been tried. This cuts out duplicate solutions and can also let people say "when you tried this did you do..." 
